designrules.description:
Eurocircuits-EAGLE design rules

Setup for 6-layer PatternClass7 BaseCopperO18-I35

The option Sizes-Minimum Drill is set to 0.35mm. This minimum drill endsize can be set lower if needed. Values below 0.25mm will result in a higher DrillClassification. For details see the Eurocircuits Classification overview.

Extra Notes:
- The option Distance-Copper/Dimension is set to 0.25mm, the default for boards with a routed boardoutline. If you require Vcut on your board this parameter should be set to 0.45mm.
- The option Supply-Generate thermals for vias is on by default but may be changed if required.
- The option Mask-Stop is set to 0mm oversize which is the preffered value.
- The option Mask-Cream is set to 0mm oversize by default, but may be changed if required
- The option Mask-Limit is set to 0.45mm, resulting in covered or tented via holes for vias of 0.45mm and smaller. The option may be changed if required.
- The options Shapes and Misc are not relevant. Values for Shapes-Smds-Roundness are not critical and can be set as you require.

You can set higher minimum values if you wish, setting lower minimum values is not advisable.
If you need lower minimum values, please use a different Eurocircuits-EAGLE design rule file. For details see the Eurocircuits-EAGLE dru overview table.

Your Eurocircuits Team
